data.text: Is a plugin that generates a mine inside a cube of various sizes with the addition of a dedicated interface that allows the interactions/collections/sales/etc of the block you have broken.
For install the plugin follow this instructions:

items.content: Open the plugin folder of your Minecraft Server;
Add CubeGenerator plugin and Vault plugin in your folder;

data.text: there are multiple type of generator not only mining blocks!
How much level you want create? Infinite!
How much you want is big the generator? Infinite!
How you want to pay? Money? Materials? Experience? All is possible!
You want a particular inventory? No Problem!
Do you like automatation? Try the automine, autosell, autofill and autokill!
1. There is a permission to place the CubeGenerator
- No, there is only a control for the space, if is enough for place it.
2. Is possible upgrade the size of the generator?
- Yes, but only when reached the max upgradable levels.
3. Is possible use the player inventory instead the custom generator inventory?
- Yes, is possible configure if you want use the custom interface (default), the player inventory, or just drop an item in config.yml.
4. What is the difference between "Respawn Delay Upgrade" and "Respawn Block Upgrade"?
- Respawn Delay Upgrade is the improvement that speeds up the respawning of blocks.
- Respawn Block Upgrade is the improvement that allows the respawning of blocks by clicking the appropriate button in the custom interface of a generator.
- You can use /cg for open an interface and get all generators created.
- You  can use /cg <configurationName> for get you a generator
- You can use /cg give for give a generator at a player
6. Is possible have a generator with mobs?
- Yes is possible configure a generator with mobs. This type of configuration is called MobGenerator, you can configure it in mobGenerator.yml and you can decide the generator type in config.yml
7. There is a possible to configure a single upgrade instead of levels?

- Yes, is possible configure a single upgrade. This type of configuration is called CustomGenerator, you can configure it in customUpgrade.yml and you can decide what generator is a CustomGenerator in config.yml.
